messages.text: The girls meet at their usual cafeteria table. Peyton comes in late and sits down without food.
Hey, where were you first period?
Late. I don‚Äôt want to be here.
None of us do. It feels wrong. I can barely sit in class.
You‚Äôre not going to eat?
Not hungry. And if one more person comes up to me to tell me they know why Ella killed herself, I‚Äôm going to snap.
What have you heard?
That she was sleeping with a teacher and he dumped her.
Oh, no. I heard that she was pregnant and couldn‚Äôt face telling her family.
That‚Äôs horrible. Do these people really think any of that could be true?
People like to think the worst. They live for drama.
Hey, I wanted to wait until we were all together to tell you‚Ä¶
Tell us what?
Well, I told Dad what we thought about Ethan.
Ok, and?
And he said they pulled up street cam footage and found them a few blocks away from the party, with Ella in his car. And then another one closer to the frat house.
What? So she was really with him?
Are they bringing him in for questioning?
They already did. There was nothing in his story that was off‚Äî
The cameras showed his car taking Ella back to her house at three that morning. He was wearing a hoodie, but they could see Ella‚Äôs face.
What else?
That‚Äôs it. He picked her up from the party. Four hours later, he dropped her off at her house.
But‚Ä¶then what?
That doesn‚Äôt explain how she died‚Äî
That doesn‚Äôt tell us why those pills were scattered across her bed.
Ella didn‚Äôt‚Ä¶
What?
Ashton‚Äôs snapchat. Look at the photo in his story‚Äî
He took it the night Ella died.
That‚Äôs at the frat house?
Yeah. They had a party.
Is that who I think it is?
Yeah. Ethan.
What‚Äôs the timestamp?
Almost one in the morning.
Look at that girl behind Ethan ‚Äî that looks like Ella‚Äôs hair.
It IS her. That‚Äôs the skirt she was wearing.
Ella was at a frat party? With her sister‚Äôs boyfriend?
Was Ava even there?
She‚Äôs not in any of these photos.
Wait. That‚Äôs not what Ella was wearing in the photo my dad showed me‚Äî
She was wearing something different at three when he took her home.
What?
Are you sure?
Positive. She wasn‚Äôt wearing that.
Does Ethan have a room at the frat house?
Yes. I asked Ashton.
Have you asked Ashton if he knows anything else?
I mean, if Ella was there, wouldn‚Äôt he have said something to you?
Maybe he didn‚Äôt see her. There are a ton of people in these photos‚Ä¶
And that‚Äôs the only one with Ethan and Ella.
So what were they doing there?
Ella‚Äôs never mentioned him, ever.
You think it‚Äôs possible something was going on that we didn‚Äôt know about?
I don‚Äôt know. But there‚Äôs another party this weekend on Halloween‚Äî
We could look around, see if we could find Ethan‚Äôs room‚Ä¶
Or ask if anyone else knows anything.
How will we get in?
Your brother‚Äôs going to recognize us ‚Äî and so will Ethan.
It‚Äôs a Halloween party. We get some wigs, some masks‚Äî
No one will even look twice at us.
You think this will work?
It will. We have to do something.
On Friday night, the girls, dressed in costumes, arrive at the fraternity party.
This is never going to work.
Sure it is. We‚Äôve made it through the front door‚Äî
That was the hardest part.
No, the hardest part is going to be getting LESS attention than we are right now.
Yeah, Peyton. Why‚Äôd you have to choose these outfits?
They make us look like Anime hookers.
Because you look so good in bubblegum pink hair down to your butt, Cass.
Yeah, and I can almost see your butt in these ridiculous skirts.
It would be hilarious if we were here for fun‚Ä¶
Quit complaining. The point was not to look like us.
Mission freaking accomplished. My own mother wouldn‚Äôt even know it was me.
And when she did, she‚Äôd drop dead.
Peyton and Kinslee both stop and stare at Cassie.
Oh. Right. Bad joke.
Come on. Let‚Äôs find out if Ethan‚Äôs here.
Well, your brother is.
Ashton? Where?
There, by the keg.
Let‚Äôs go the other way.
You know he‚Äôs staring at us, right?
You think he recognizes us?
Oh, God.
What? Is our cover blown?
Worse.
What‚Äôs worse than that?
I know that look.
Just spit it out, Peyton!
That grin. That‚Äôs his charming face.
Why would your brother be looking at us with his‚Ä¶oh, you‚Äôre kidding.
Nope. Run. Hide. Now.
If your brother tries to hit on you, Peyton, I‚Äôm going to fall on the floor laughing.
Like, I almost want to see that ‚Äî just to see you try to keep your cool and play along.
No way in hell. Look, there are the stairs. Move.
Look, there‚Äôs Ethan.
Who‚Äôs he talking to? Wait. Is that‚Ä¶?
Why is Mr. Stevens here?
I‚Äôm seeing things, right? Like, is our history teacher really at a frat party?
Peyton reaches out and grabs the nearest guy.
Hey, who is Ethan talking to?
Um, that‚Äôs our alumni sponsor.
Mr. Stevens?
Yeah, he‚Äôs always around.
The boy walks away and Cassie turns to her friends.
Guys, cameras ‚Äî Mr. Stevens told Ethan he could pull up the cameras for proof.
Does that mean the house has them? We could see what Ella did here.
He‚Äôs looking this way. You two, see if you can get upstairs.
I‚Äôll see if I can get closer to them, and distract Ethan if I need to.
Your brother‚Äôs coming this way, too.
Just go ‚Äî now!
Before this all falls apart‚Ä¶
